        <p><strong>Where Frase wins:</strong> if your bottleneck is "what do I tell my writer?", the brief builder is unmatched. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your bottleneck is "I don't have a writer". Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Frase?</h2>
        <p>Frase is an AI-powered SEO content research and optimization platform founded in 2017 by Tomas Ratia and headquartered in Boston. The platform scrapes the top-ranking search results for any keyword and extracts competitor headings, word counts, question coverage, and topic gaps — then assembles them into a content brief automatically.</p>

        <p>The core suite does four things:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Content Brief Builder</strong> — turns any keyword into a structured outline in 10–20 minutes</li>
          <li><strong>AI Writer</strong> — 80+ writing skills that draft article scaffolds</li>
          <li><strong>Content Score</strong> — grades drafts against top-ranking competitors</li>
          <li><strong>Content Audit (GSC)</strong> — pulls your existing pages and surfaces quick wins</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Frase is <em>not</em>: a writing service, a CMS, or a publishing platform. It shows you what to write. Capturing the traffic is on you.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Frase raised $1.2M in seed funding back in 2018 and has stayed independent since. The 2024 platform rebuild was a major version jump — and it created friction with lifetime deal purchasers who felt cut off from the new product. Worth knowing if you're considering a long-term commitment.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Frase features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is focused — research, briefs, AI writing, scoring. Here's what actually matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. Content Brief Builder — the crown jewel</h3>
        <p>Enter a keyword. Frase returns:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Top 20 ranking pages with their full outlines extracted (H1, H2, H3)</li>
          <li>Aggregate word count benchmarks across the top 10</li>
          <li>Common questions from People Also Ask, Quora, Reddit</li>
          <li>Topic coverage gaps — terms ranked content covers that you don't</li>
          <li>One-click brief generation with all the above pre-filled</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The brief builder is where Frase genuinely separates from Surfer, Clearscope, and MarketMuse. For a freelancer producing 10–20 briefs a month, this alone saves hours that pay for the subscription many times over.</p>

        <h3>2. AI Writer — drafts, not finished articles</h3>
        <p>Frase's AI writer ships with 80+ skills (blog intros, product descriptions, meta descriptions, FAQ blocks, etc.) and a full long-form editor. Output quality is competent but generic — expect <strong>30–60 minutes of editing per draft</strong> before it's ready to publish. The AI saves you from the blank page; it doesn't save you from the editing chair.</p>

        <h3>3. Content Score — optimization grading</h3>
        <p>Frase scores your draft against the top-ranking competitors for your target keyword. Topic coverage, word count, header density, and entity inclusion all roll up into a single 0–100 score. The catch: ranking correlation is <strong>0.10</strong>, vs Surfer SEO's 0.28. Frase's score is a useful directional signal — Surfer's is more predictive.</p>

        <h3>4. Content Audit — GSC integration</h3>
        <p>Connect Google Search Console and Frase pulls every URL you own, sorts them by current rank, and flags pages on positions 11–30 — the quick-win zone. Users report finding 12+ optimization opportunities per audit. This is the most underrated feature in the product.</p>

        <h3>5. AI Visibility Tracking</h3>
        <p>Tracks brand and content appearance in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews. Early-stage but useful if you're trying to get cited in AI answers — a channel that matters more every month.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Frase pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Frase publishes pricing. Most reviews quote the sticker. We'll quote the <em>full</em> cost — sticker plus everything you have to bolt on to actually publish content.</p>

