        <h2 id="verdict">Is Frase worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For freelance writers and agencies: yes.</strong> The brief builder genuinely cuts research time from 90 minutes to 10. If you bill clients per article, the Basic plan ($129/mo) pays for itself in saved hours by week one.</p>

        <p><strong>For in-house content teams: yes, with a caveat.</strong> You'll likely want Surfer SEO on top — Frase's content score has a 0.10 ranking correlation, Surfer's is 0.28. Total tooling cost: $228–$398/mo before writers.</p>

        <p><strong>For small business owners: almost always no.</strong> You open Frase. You build a beautiful brief. You realize you need to write the article. You don't have time. The brief sits in a folder. You would spend $49/mo collecting briefs you never publish.</p>

